FBIS4-16516 "drsov074_o_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-074 Daily Report 16 Apr 1994 Uzbekistan Uzbekistan Afghan Claims of Aid to Opposition Uzbekistan Afghan Claims of Aid to Opposition PM1804103394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 16 Apr 94 First Edition p 6 PM1804103394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Report from roundup of ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA and ITAR-TASS reports: "Kabul's Accusations Denied"] [Text] Afghanistan has accused Uzbekistan of supporting the opponent of the country's president, Borhanoddin Rabbani, that is Prime Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar, and his ally General Dustum -- an ethnic Uzbek whose troops also consist of Uzbeks. Kabul radio yesterday broadcast a statement by the Afghan intelligence leadership to the effect that Tashkent has given Dustum aircraft to bomb the Afghan capital and this week they have already struck against Kabul. Surat Mirkasymov, Uzbekistan charge d'affaires ad interim to India, has categorically denied the Afghan intelligence service's statement.
